<div id="review_1169436030" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1169436030" />
    <a title="Gary Pearson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/30707904-gary-pearson"><img alt="Gary Pearson" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1537483772p2/30707904.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1169436030?book_show_action=true">Jan 15, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gary Pearson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gary Pearson" href="/user/show/30707904-gary-pearson">Gary Pearson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1169436030" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11791644494501916674">The Copy was a brilliant short read that had a lot within it. The chapters flow extremely well focusing on either the courtroom drama or the past, all of it linking seamlessly into one another. <br/><br/>The chapters were punchy and every time I got to the end of one I had to read on to find out what was going to happen.<br/><br/>I will be looking for more of the authors work in the future because of this.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


